        "content": "Machine learning is a core discipline within artificial intelligence, focused on enabling computers to perform tasks without relying on predetermined rules. Instead of being explicitly programmed for every scenario, ML systems use algorithms to identify patterns and make data-driven decisions.\n\nThese systems learn and improve from experience by processing large amounts of data. The core principle is that through iterative exposure to data, the model's algorithm adjusts its internal parameters to enhance its performance on a specific task."
      }
